⎩392⎭
⎩393⎭
⎩394⎭
  subr (literal) {⎩395⎭
      ⌈⎩396⎭
   Inside definitions only, pushes compiled literal to stack ⎩397⎭
⎩398⎭
       Certain Forth words are only applicable inside compiled sequences of subroutines ⎩399⎭
       Literals are handled in different ways when interpreted when in the REPL vs⎩400⎭
       compiled into sequences of subrs ⎩401⎭
       In the REPL, when we encounter a literal, we simply push it onto the stack ⎩402⎭
       In the compiler, though, we have to create an instruction that pushes ⎩403⎭
	 the literal onto the stack. ⎩404⎭
	 Compiled code doesn't do what the REPL does, we have to hard-wire and ⎩405⎭
	 bake in code that pushes the literal when the time comes to run the sequence. ⎩406⎭
⎩407⎭
       This word - "(literal)" - is a simple case and one could actually type this ⎩408⎭
	 instruction into the REPL, but, that would be redundant.  Other kinds of words, ⎩409⎭
	 e.g. some control-flow words, tend to be messier and the code below only handles ⎩410⎭
	 the compiled aspects and ignores the REPL aspects ⎩411⎭
⎩412⎭
       "IP" is the current word index in a sequence of words being compiled. ⎩413⎭
  ⌉⎩414⎭
      defsynonym lit ≡ State.RAM [State.IP]⎩415⎭
      %push (lit)⎩416⎭
      State.IP ⇐ State.IP + 1 ⌈ move past this item (the literal) - we're done with it ⌉⎩417⎭
  }⎩418⎭
⎩419⎭
  subr branch {⎩420⎭
      ⌈ This instruction appears only inside subroutine sequences, jump to address in next cell ⌉⎩421⎭
      ⌈ This instruction is inserted into a subr sequence when compiling control-flow words, like "else" see below) ⌉⎩422⎭
      State.IP ⇐ State.RAM [State.IP]⎩423⎭
      ⌈ normally, we just execute an instruction then move the IP sequentially forward by 1 unit, i.e. IP ⇐ IP + 1 ⌉⎩424⎭
      ⌈   in this case, though, we explicitly change the IP to some other value and don't just increment it ⌉⎩425⎭
  }⎩426⎭
⎩427⎭
  subr 0branch {⎩428⎭
      ⌈ This instruction appears only inside subroutine sequences, jump on false to address in next cell ⌉⎩429⎭
      deftemp test ⇐ %toboolean (%pop)⎩430⎭
      if (test) {⎩431⎭
	  State.IP ⇐ State.IP + 1⎩432⎭
      } else {⎩433⎭
	 State.IP ⇐ State.RAM [State.IP]⎩434⎭
      }⎩435⎭
  }⎩436⎭
⎩437⎭
⎩438⎭
  ⌈ "immediate" words are fully operational even when in compile mode. Some (not all) of these words are meant to⎩439⎭
      work /only/ in compile mode. At the REPL prompt ("interpret" mode), they produce unwanted results.⎩440⎭
    immediate words: xif, xelse, xthen, xquote, xcomment, xsemi⎩441⎭
    immediate words that only have meaning in compile mode: xif, xelse, xthen, xsemi⎩442⎭
  ⌉⎩443⎭
⎩444⎭
⎩445⎭
  ⌈ IF, ELSE and THEN are "immediate" words - they should only be used inside of ":" (colon compiler) ⌉⎩446⎭
⎩447⎭
  ⌈ see diagram compiling-IF-THEN.drawio.png ⌉⎩448⎭
  subr %immediate ❲if❳ { ⎩449⎭
      ⌈ This instruction appears only inside subroutine sequences, ( f -- ) compile if test and branchFalse ⌉ ⎩450⎭
      ⌈ Step. 1: generate conditional branch to yet-unknown target1 ⌉ ⎩451⎭
      deftemp branchFalseAddress ⇐ %funcall _find ("0branch")⎩452⎭
      %ram+ (branchFalseAddress) ⌈ insert branch-if-false opcode (word) ⌉ ⎩453⎭
      %rpush (%RAMnext) ⌈ target1 onto r-stack as memo for later fixup ⌉ ⎩454⎭
      defsynonym target1 ≡ -1 ⎩455⎭
      %ram+ (target1) ⌈ branch target will be fixed up later ⌉ ⎩456⎭
      ⌈ Step. 2: generate code for true branch - return to compiler which will compile the following words ⌉ ⎩457⎭
      ⌈ THEN or ELSE will do the fixup of target1 ⌉ ⎩458⎭
  }⎩459⎭
⎩460⎭
  ⌈ see diagram compiling-IF-ELSE-THEN.drawio.png ⌉⎩461⎭
  subr %immediate ❲else❳ {⎩462⎭
      ⌈ Step. 1: fixup target1 from IF-true, retrieving memo from R-stack ⌉⎩463⎭
      deftemp target1 ⇐ %rpop⎩464⎭
      State.RAM [target1] ⇐ %RAMnext⎩465⎭
      ⌈ Step. 2: generate unconditional branch for preceding IF, creating new memo for target2 on R-stack ⌉⎩466⎭
      deftemp brAddress ⇐ %funcall _find ("branch")⎩467⎭
      %rpush (%RAMnext) ⌈ target2 address on R-stack as memo for later fixup ⌉⎩468⎭
      defsynonym target2 ≡ -1⎩469⎭
      %ram+ (target2) ⌈ branch target will be fixed up later ⌉⎩470⎭
      ⌈ Step. 3: generate code for false branch - return to compiler which will compile the following words ⌉⎩471⎭
      ⌈ THEN will do the fixup of target2 ⌉⎩472⎭
  }⎩473⎭
⎩474⎭
  ⌈ see diagrams compiling-IF-THEN.drawio.png and compiling-IF-ELSE-THEN.drawio.png ⌉⎩475⎭
  subr %immediate ❲then❳ {⎩476⎭
      ⌈ Step. 1: fixup target (from IF or from ELSE, above), retrieving memo from R-stack ⌉⎩477⎭
      deftemp target ⇐ %rpop⎩478⎭
      State.RAM [target] ⇐ %RAMnext⎩479⎭
  }⎩480⎭
⎩481⎭
  subr (do) {⎩482⎭
      ⌈ ( limit index --) Puts limit and index on return stack. ⌉⎩483⎭
      @xswap⎩484⎭
      deftemp index ⇐ %pop⎩485⎭
      deftemp limit ⇐ %pop⎩486⎭
      %rpush (index)⎩487⎭
      %rpush (limit)⎩488⎭
  }⎩489⎭
⎩490⎭
  subr %immediate ❲do❳ {⎩491⎭
      ⌈ (  limit index --) Begin counted loop. ⌉⎩492⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("(do)"))  ⌈ Push do loop handler. ⌉⎩493⎭
      %rpush(%RAMnext)           ⌈ Push address to jump back to. ⌉⎩494⎭
  }⎩495⎭
⎩496⎭
  subr (loop) {⎩497⎭
      ⌈ (  -- f) Determine if loop is done. ⌉⎩498⎭
      deftemp index ⇐ %rpop⎩499⎭
      deftemp limit ⇐ %rpop⎩500⎭
      defsynonym cond ≡ (index >= limit)⎩501⎭
      %push (cond)⎩502⎭
      if (cond) { ⌈ clean up rstack if index >= limit ⌉⎩503⎭
	  %rpop⎩504⎭
	  %rpop⎩505⎭
      }  ⎩506⎭
  }⎩507⎭
⎩508⎭
  subr %immediate +loop {⎩509⎭
      ⌈ ( --) Close counted loop. ⌉⎩510⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("(loop)"))   ⌈ Compile in loop test. ⌉⎩511⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("0branch"))  ⌈ Compile in branch check. ⌉⎩512⎭
      %ram+(%rpop)           ⌈ Address to jump back to. ⌉⎩513⎭
  }⎩514⎭
⎩515⎭
  subr %immediate ❲loop❳ {⎩516⎭
      ⌈ (  --) Close counted loop. ⌉⎩517⎭
      %push (1)⎩518⎭
      @literalize                  ⌈ Default loop increment for x_loop. ⌉⎩519⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("(loop)"))   ⌈ Compile in loop test. ⌉⎩520⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("0branch"))  ⌈ Compile in branch check. ⌉⎩521⎭
      %ram+(%rpop)           ⌈ Address to jump back to. ⌉⎩522⎭
  }⎩523⎭
⎩524⎭
  subr %immediate ❲begin❳ {⎩525⎭
      %rpush (%RAMnext)  ⌈ ( --) Start indefinite loop. ⌉⎩526⎭
  }⎩527⎭
⎩528⎭
  subr %immediate ❲until❳ {⎩529⎭
      ⌈ (  f --) Close indefinite loop with test. ⌉⎩530⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("0branch"))  ⌈ Expects result of test on stack. ⌉⎩531⎭
      %ram+(%rpop)           ⌈ Address to jump back to. ⌉⎩532⎭
  }⎩533⎭
⎩534⎭
⎩535⎭
⎩536⎭
  ⌈  "... 123 constant K ..." ⌉⎩537⎭
  ⌈  at interpretation time: 123 is on the Stack, we have consumed "constant" from BUFF, BUFF now contains "K ..." ⌉⎩538⎭
  ⌈  invoke 'word' which parses "K" and pushed it. The stack becomes [... 123 "K"] ⌉⎩539⎭
  ⌈  pop "K", pop 123, create a new word called 'K' with its PFA set to 123 and its CFA set to a subr that⎩540⎭
       gets 123 from its PFA and pushes it onto the stack ⌉⎩541⎭
  subr ❲const❳ {⎩542⎭
      ⌈  get next word - the name - from BUFF ⌉⎩543⎭
      defsynonym blank ≡ 32⎩544⎭
      %push (blank)⎩545⎭
      @xword⎩546⎭
      ⌈  stack is now: ( NNNN name -- ) ⌉⎩547⎭
      deftemp name ⇐ %pop⎩548⎭
      deftemp value ⇐ %pop⎩549⎭
      defsynonym normal ≡ 0⎩550⎭
      deftemp fobj ⇐ %funcall code (name, normal, ↪︎doconst)⎩551⎭
      %ram+ (value)⎩552⎭
  }⎩553⎭
⎩554⎭
  subr , {⎩555⎭
      %funcall comma (%pop)⎩556⎭
  }⎩557⎭
⎩558⎭
  subr variable {⎩559⎭
      defsynonym blank ≡ 32⎩560⎭
      %push (blank)⎩561⎭
      @xword⎩562⎭
      deftemp name ⇐ %pop⎩563⎭
      deftemp value ⇐ %pop⎩564⎭
      %funcall fvar (name, value)    ⎩565⎭
  }⎩566⎭
⎩567⎭
  subr dump {⎩568⎭
      deftemp n ⇐ %toint (%pop)⎩569⎭
      deftemp start ⇐ %toint (%pop)⎩570⎭
      %print ("----------------------------------------------------------------")⎩571⎭
      deftemp a ⇐ start⎩572⎭
      while (a < start + (%funcall min (n, (%funcall len (State.RAM) - start)))) {⎩573⎭
	  %print (a)⎩574⎭
	  %print (": ")⎩575⎭
	  %print (State.RAM [a])⎩576⎭
	  %eol⎩577⎭
	  deftemp a ⇐ a + 1⎩578⎭
      }⎩579⎭
  }⎩580⎭
⎩581⎭
  subr ! {⎩582⎭
      deftemp b ⇐ %pop⎩583⎭
      deftemp a ⇐ %pop⎩584⎭
      State.RAM [b] ⇐ a⎩585⎭
  }⎩586⎭
⎩587⎭
  subr bye { ⌈ ( --) Leave interpreter ⌉ %quit }⎩588⎭
⎩589⎭
⎩590⎭
  subr find {⎩591⎭
      ⌈ "( name | -- (name 0)|(xt 1)|(xt -1)) Search for word name." ⌉⎩592⎭
      ⌈ 3 possible results: 1. (name 0) if not found, 2. (xt 1) if found and word is immediate, 3. (xt -1) if found and word is normal ⌉⎩593⎭
      %push (32)⎩594⎭
      @xword⎩595⎭
      deftemp found ⇐ %funcall _find(%stop)⎩596⎭
      if (0 = found) {⎩597⎭
	  %push (0)⎩598⎭
      } else {⎩599⎭
	  %pop  ⌈ # Get rid of name on stack. ⌉⎩600⎭
	  %push(found)⎩601⎭
	  deftemp immediate ⇐ -1⎩602⎭
	  if (State.RAM[%stop - 1] & 1) { immediate ⇐ 1 }⎩603⎭
	  %push(immediate)⎩604⎭
      }⎩605⎭
  }⎩606⎭
⎩607⎭
  subr ' {⎩608⎭
      ⌈ "( name -- xt|-1) Search for execution token of word name." ⌉⎩609⎭
      %push (32)⎩610⎭
      @xword⎩611⎭
      deftemp name ⇐ %pop⎩612⎭
      deftemp found ⇐ %funcall _find(name)⎩613⎭
      %push (found)⎩614⎭
  }⎩615⎭
⎩616⎭
  subr None {⎩617⎭
      %pushNone⎩618⎭
  }⎩619⎭
⎩620⎭
  subr words {⎩621⎭
      ⌈ print words in dictionary ⌉⎩622⎭
      deftemp x ⇐ State.LAST⎩623⎭
      while (x > -1) {⎩624⎭
	  %print (State.RAM [x+ 1])⎩625⎭
	  %print (" ")⎩626⎭
      }⎩627⎭
      %eol⎩628⎭
  }⎩629⎭
⎩630⎭
⎩631⎭
  subr execute {⎩632⎭
      ⌈ invoke given word ⌉⎩633⎭
      deftemp wordAddress ⇐ %pop⎩634⎭
      @@wordAddress⎩635⎭
  }⎩636⎭
⎩637⎭
⎩638⎭
  subr : {⎩639⎭
      ⌈ ( name | --) Start compilation. ⌉⎩640⎭
      defsynonym blank ≡ 32⎩641⎭
      %push (blank)⎩642⎭
      @xword⎩643⎭
      deftemp name ⇐ %pop⎩644⎭
      %funcall code(name, 0, doword)⎩645⎭
      %setCompilingState⎩646⎭
  }⎩647⎭
⎩648⎭
  subr %immediate ; {⎩649⎭
      ⌈ ( --) Finish definition. ⌉⎩650⎭
⎩651⎭
      %ram+(-1)  ⌈ Marker for end of definition. ⌉⎩652⎭
      %setNotCompilingState⎩653⎭
  }⎩654⎭
⎩655⎭
  subr interpret {⎩656⎭
      ⌈ ( string --) Execute word. ⌉⎩657⎭
⎩658⎭
      @find⎩659⎭
      ⌈ 3 possible results from find:⎩660⎭
	  1. (name 0) if not found,⎩661⎭
	  2. (xt 1) if found and word is immediate,⎩662⎭
	  3. (xt -1) if found and word is normal ⌉⎩663⎭
      deftemp result ⇐ %pop					    defsynonym foundimmediate ≡ (result = 1)⎩664⎭
      deftemp item ⇐ %pop						    defsynonym foundnormal ≡ (result = -1)⎩665⎭
								      defsynonym notfound ≡ (result = 0)⎩666⎭
								      defsynonym found ≡ (foundimmediate or foundnormal)⎩667⎭
⎩668⎭
if (found) {⎩669⎭
    if (%incompilingstate) {⎩670⎭
        if (foundimmediate) {⎩671⎭
            λexec(item)⎩672⎭
        } else {⎩673⎭
            λcompileword(item)⎩674⎭
        }⎩675⎭
        ⎩676⎭
    } else {⎩677⎭
        λexec(item)⎩678⎭
    }⎩679⎭
    ⎩680⎭
} else {⎩681⎭
    if (%incompilingstate) {⎩682⎭
        if (%isinteger(item)) {⎩683⎭
            λcompileinteger(item)⎩684⎭
        } else {⎩685⎭
            if (%isfloat(item)) {⎩686⎭
                λcompilefloat(item)⎩687⎭
            } else {⎩688⎭
                @returnFalse⎩689⎭
            }⎩690⎭
            ⎩691⎭
        }⎩692⎭
        ⎩693⎭
    } else {⎩694⎭
        if (%isinteger(item)) {⎩695⎭
            λpushasinteger(item)⎩696⎭
        } else {⎩697⎭
            if (%isfloat(item)) {⎩698⎭
                λpushasfloat(item)⎩699⎭
            } else {⎩700⎭
                @returnFalse⎩701⎭
            }⎩702⎭
            ⎩703⎭
        }⎩704⎭
        ⎩705⎭
    }⎩706⎭
    ⎩707⎭
}⎩708⎭
⎩709⎭
      return True⎩710⎭
}⎩711⎭
}⎩712⎭
⎩713⎭
invoke {⎩714⎭
  @ok⎩715⎭
}⎩716⎭